<exercise id="fs-idm46455776">
<problem id="fs-idp48525360">
<para id="fs-idp69216848">Although PF<sub>5</sub> and AsF<sub>5</sub> are stable, nitrogen does not form NF<sub>5</sub> molecules. Explain this difference among members of the same group.</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idp47327840">
<para id="fs-idp203262192">Nitrogen cannot form a NF<sub>5</sub> molecule because it does not have <emphasis effect="italics">d</emphasis> orbitals to bond with the additional two fluorine atoms.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
